.TH "KWIM" "1" "2026-04-19" "kwim" "kwm input manager"
.PP
.SH NAME
.PP
kwim - kwm input manager for River Wayland compositor
.PP
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\fBkwim\fR [OPTION]
.br
\fBkwim\fR \fBSUBCOMMAND\fR \fIDEVICE_TYPE\fR \fIDEVICE_OPTION\fR.\&.\&.\& [ARG].\&.\&.\&
.PP
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
\fIkwm\fR is a DWM-like dynamic tiling window manager implementing the
river-window-management-v1 protocol.\&
.PP
\fBkwim\fR is an input manager separated from \fIkwm\fR, implementing the
river-input-management-v1 protocol and/or related protocols in order to
configure input devices independent of window manager.\&
.PP
\fIkwm\fR will automatically run \fBkwim\fR at startup.\& You can also run \fBkwim\fR to list
input devices or apply a single rule on demand.\&
.PP
Without any subcommands and options, \fBkwim\fR reads input rules from the same
configuration file used by \fIkwm\fR.\&
.PP
.SH OPTIONS
.PP
\fB-h,--help\fR
.RS 4
Print a help message and exit.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB-v,--version\fR
.RS 4
Print the version and exit.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB-c,--config\fR
.RS 4
Specify the configuration file path.\&
.PP
.RE
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.PP
\fBlist\fR
.RS 4
Lists all connected devices of the specified type.\&
.PP
.RE
\fBapply\fR
.RS 4
Applies configuration rules to a specific device type.\&
.PP
.RE
.SH DEVICE\_TYPE
.PP
\fBinput-device\fR
.PP
\fBlibinput-device\fR
.PP
